Introduction

ALL(H)OURS, also written as ALL HOURS, is a South Korean boy group under Eden Entertainment. The group made their debut with the mini album "ALL OURS" on January 10, 2024. It consists of seven members: Kunho, Yumin, Xayden, Minje, Masami, Hyunbin, and ON:N.

The group’s name has a dual meaning of “all ours (everything we have)” and “all hours (always, every moment)”, reflecting their ambition to show their diverse talents and charms to the world.
